'The cops were really worried, they were anxious. We heard the words "attempt to murder" and "weapon",' she said. 

Police early on Friday said in a statement that a  Preston man had been charged with attempted murder and causing serious injury following a firearms incident.

The man has been remanded in custody and will appear in Melbourne Magistrates Court later on Friday.

